
// The code demonstrates how to use the [strings.builder] slot to construct a string by appending multiple segments. It appends the value from the [table] argument, a colon character, and the value from the [id] argument sequentially. This approach allows for dynamic string construction based on input arguments.
strings.builder
   strings.builder.append:x:@.arguments/*/table
   strings.builder.append:":"
   strings.builder.append:x:@.arguments/*/id
